{
  "text": "Here, a finite element is subdivided into cells, each of which contains an integration point ( Figure 1 ). The integration point is assigned the cell average of the underlying random field. This way of discretization of the random field is consistent with local averaging theory [CITATION_1] in taking account of the variance reduction as a result of spatial averaging. Withz being the cell average of random field values z( x), the exact solution of the variance reduction factor \u03b3 = E[z 2 ]/E[z 2 ] is found by",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "119458111"
